AGI -&nbsp; The project was presented today at the Press Office of the Sacred Convent of San Francesco in Assisi: "Assisi Terra Laudato Si'", animated by the Centro Laudato Si' of Assisi for the diffusion of the values of integral ecology > and promoted in collaboration with the main institutional, civil and religious realities of the city. The project was born in preparation for the "Giubileo Laudato Si'" of 2025, the double anniversary of the 800 years of the Cantico delle Creature> and the 10 years of the encyclical Laudato Si', to offer the pilgrims the opportunity to know in depth these two messages of Francis of Assisi and Francis of Rome.
<br After the announcement last year by the Bishop of Assisi Monsignor Domenico Sorrentino together with Cardinal Michael Czerny of the Vatican, now the project is ready to start receiving pilgrims. This proposal was born to respond to the ever-increasing need for sensitization, training, and spirituality > aimed not only at those engaged in the themes of integral ecology, but at all. Assisi, for its deep symbolic meaning and its bond with St. Francis, patron of ecology worshipers, as indicated by St. John Paul II, has great potential to announce and promote this message for the whole world. The proposal that is launched on Earth Day, April 22, is promoted in a choral way by the whole city, and by its various souls: from the Diocese of Assisi to the Franciscan families, from Pro Civitate Christiana to Fai; it will also actively involve associations, educational institutions and the different souls of civil society. The project will be coordinated by the Laudato Si' Centre, the Assyrian headquarters of the Laudato Si'.&nbsp Movement;
&nbsp;
The project was presented by Antonio Caschetto and Tomas Insua (Centro Laudato Si' di Assisi), along with Marina Rosati (director of communications office of the diocese of Assisi) who outlined the synodal path and future perspectives of the project, and to Brother Giulio Cesareo, director of the Communication Office of the Sacred Convent of St. Francis, who offered a look on the Franciscan spirituality that is the soul of the project. At the meeting was also the mayor of Assisi, Stefania Proietti.
<br> "Assisi Terra Laudato Si'", as specified in the site AssisiLaudatoSi.org, will offer the city a series of programs and initiatives that aim to spread the values of integral ecology. For example, through the Laudato Ritiri you' lived not only in the Franciscan shrines, but in the whole city and its ecosystem (composed of the landscape, colors, silences and the unique spirituality that you breathe here), the pilgrims will have the opportunity to better know the figure of St. Francis> through the words of the Canticle of Creature. Moreover, in the "Laudato Si' places" (both places that have seen the various stages of the composition of the Canticle of Sun Friars, both places that present it), guided prayer paths. Training courses and screening of the film "La Lettera: A Message for our Earth", which tells the story of the encyclical Laudato si' with Pope Francis. The docu-film is presented by YouTube Originals, and produced by Off The Fence Productions (winners Oscar 2021) and the Laudato Si' Movement. Finally, a volunteer service will be activated to the project initiatives.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Among the activities that will carry out the volunteers, there will be the accompaniment of the retreats, the support to the events of prayer and formation, and moments of work and prayer in the countryside around. This project will be inaugurated with a rich series of events. The previous days will be animated by the artistic performance entitled "Custodi della Terra, artisans of Peace", edited by Francesco Astiaso Garcia (Catholic Union Italian artists) that will involve pilgrims, tourists and parishes. The performance consists of a collective painting experience, in preparation for Earth Day. The overall installation, with the works of each, will constitute a real "Grido di Pace" that will rise from Assisi. Moreover, always to celebrate the Earth, on Sunday 21 April the Fai will propose two paths in the Bosco di S. Francesco entitled "Festeggiamo madre Terra".
&nbsp;
On 22 April, at the Citadel Laudato Si', two moments are planned. In the morning, at 11 o'clock there will be the inauguration of the project Assisi Terra Laudato Si', where will intervene, among others, Vito Stanzione del Cnr, > engaged in Antarctica on climate detection activities; the Franciscan nun Mary Frances Traynor, who will tell his experience from the first Earth Day, lived in Wisconsin in 1970; Susana Refega, the new international director of the Laudato Si' Movement. It will be an opportunity to share the competition on integral ecology, promoted by the Citadel Laudato Si' and intended for Italian schools. The event will be lived in connection with the Earth Day Italia #OnePeopleOnePlanet marathon. At the end of the Day as it happens for a few years, at 18.30 there will be an interreligious moment of spirituality and contemplation of sunset, in the presence of Monsignor Domenico Sorrentino with members of different Christian confessions and religious traditions. &nbsp;

