AGI - The island of Capri is secured, island-joy in front of Naples, which today welcomes the meeting of the Foreign Ministers of the G7, which will last until Friday. To ensure security, at a time of great international tension - after <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-04-16/israele-responde-ad-iranian-26037904/"> Iran's attack on Israel</a> and fear of a imminent response from the Jewish State - measures have been amplified: 1400 men deployed, not only police officers, in addition to the local ones, but also carabinieri, firefighters (who supplied the divers) and bourgeois agents everywhere; cynofile units, helicopters, almost every specialty of law enforcement, including bombers. To ensure the safety of the delegations and the events planned, the forces of the order preside over all the nerves of the island.&nbsp; Of course, there are strengthened controls at access gates in the area of the summit, check point at the port and in the center, drones that guard from above > precisely to prevent any kind of threat. The forces of the order are a discreet presence also on ferries and hydrofoils, precisely to control arrivals.
&nbsp;
On the sea the surveillance is entrusted to the Harbour office and the Guardia di Finanza, for all three days there will be ban of docking in Marina Grande, a motorvedetta presides over the stretch of waters overlooking the Blue Grotto >. It is obviously protected air space over the island. Security devices strengthened also in Naples, at the pier of the boards; the presidi in sensitive points, such as synagogues and places of worship, were intensified. In Capri, some areas, from today, are off limits, with transit prohibitions also to facilitate the displacement of delegations and ensure the fluidity of any aid. The health plan has also been strengthened to ensure immediate medical care in case of need, with ambulances but also an elixoccorso service.
